# Parsing Timeouts

## Background

`Complex regular subexpression recursion limit`

> 2023-04-23T23:31:31.9936518Z Complex regular subexpression recursion limit (65534) exceeded at /usr/local/share/perl/5.34.0/CheckSpelling/UnknownWordSplitter.pm line 372, <FILE> in tests/ui/parser/slowparse-bstring.rs - line 6.

https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rust-lang/rust/f65615f02d22b85e9205f2716ab36182d34bab2b/tests/ui/parser/slowparse-bstring.rs#L6
```rs
fn main() { b""; }
```

Parsing a single file with this line can take over an hour if not limited.

## Solution

https://perldoc.perl.org/functions/alarm

## Configuration

There is not currently a `with` field for this, but you can use:

```yaml
env:
  splitter_timeout: ...
```
... to provide a splitter_timeout. The default is `30` (seconds) per file.
